  <!-- 11. HOW WE REPAIR -->
  <section class="process">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading section-heading-light">
        <span class="section-num">07</span>
        <h2>How Our Technicians Repair a Bosch Washer</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="process-grid">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <h3>Read the Code and the Symptoms Together</h3>
          <p>A Bosch E-code narrows the problem but doesn't finish the
          diagnosis. E18 tells us the washer can't drain — not why. We check
          pump filter, pump motor, drain hose, and outlet line before replacing
          anything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <h3>Test, Don't Guess</h3>
          <p>Before a pump gets replaced, we meter the motor windings. Before
          a pressure switch goes in, we test the air dome tube first (90% of
          E04s are a clogged tube, not a bad switch). Bosch parts aren't cheap
          — no throwing money at the wrong component.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <h3>Manufacturer-Approved Parts Only</h3>
          <p>Aftermarket door boots, inlet valves, and control boards fail
          within 18 months on hard water. We install only Bosch
          manufacturer-approved parts from authorized distributors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <h3>Address the Cause, Not Just the Failure</h3>
          <p>An inlet valve that clogged in year 4 points to hard water. We
          suggest a softener or at minimum a filter. A door boot that tore in
          year 3 means underwires or loose buttons — we flag laundry practice
          to prevent repeat.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <h3>Test the Full Cycle Before We Leave</h3>
          <p>We don't close a ticket until the washer runs a full cycle — fill,
          wash, drain, spin — with clothing in it. Final check every time.
          Catches the 1 in 50 cases where a second component failed during
          repair.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">6</div>
          <h3>90-Day Labor Warranty, 1-Year on Parts</h3>
          <p>Every Bosch washer repair carries a 90-day labor warranty and
          1-year warranty on installed manufacturer-approved parts. Same issue
          recurs, we come back at no charge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

